.TH custome _printf "16 Mar 2021" "_printf man page"

.SH NAME
_printf

.SH DESCRIPTION
This program emulates the standard C printf function. it takes
a formating string and a variable number of values to be 
displayed. on successful completion it returns the number of 
characters displayed. 

.SH CONVERSION SPECIFIERS
.IP %S
prints string of characters
.IP %c
print a single character
.IP %d
print decimal value (base 10) number
.IP %i
print an integer in base 10
.IP %u
print an unsigned decimal (base 10) number
.IP %x
print a number in hexadecimal (base 16)
.IP %o
print a number in octal (base 8)
,IP %r
print a string reversed
.IP %R
print a string converted to rot13

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B To use the _printf function first add #include "holberton.h" to your program
.B To print using _printf for example,
.I To print "ALX Program" and 2021 where the first on is a pointer to string and the second one is an integer:

.I _printf("%s, %d\n", "ALX Program", 2021);


